      "question": "If $\\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle PQR$ and $\\frac{AB}{PQ} = \\frac{1}{3}$, then the ratio $\\frac{ar(\\triangle ABC)}{ar(\\triangle PQR)}$ is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "According to the area of similar triangles theorem, the ratio of areas is equal to the square of the ratio of their corresponding sides.",
          "The ratio of sides is $\\frac{1}{3}$.",
          "Square of the ratio is $(\\frac{1}{3})^2 = \\frac{1}{9}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{ar(\\triangle ABC)}{ar(\\triangle PQR)} = (\\frac{AB}{PQ})^2 = (\\frac{1}{3})^2 = \\frac{1}{9}$"
      },
