      "question": "If $\\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DEF$, $\\angle A = 50^\\circ$, and $\\angle E = 70^\\circ$, then $\\angle C$ is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Since $\\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DEF$, corresponding angles are equal: $\\angle A = \\angle D$, $\\angle B = \\angle E$, $\\angle C = \\angle F$.",
          "Given $\\angle E = 70^\\circ$, so $\\angle B = 70^\\circ$.",
          "In $\\triangle ABC$, $\\angle A + \\angle B + \\angle C = 180^\\circ$.",
          "$50^\\circ + 70^\\circ + \\angle C = 180^\\circ$.",
          "$\\angle C = 180^\\circ - 120^\\circ = 60^\\circ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\angle C = 180^\\circ - (\\angle A + \\angle B) = 180^\\circ - (50^\\circ + 70^\\circ) = 60^\\circ$"
      },
